---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Docs — SEOplant"
  description="Learn how to use SEOplant to research competitors, build SEO strategies, generate content, and deploy ranking websites."
>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:800px;">

      <h1>Documentation</h1>

      <p style="font-size:1.1rem; color:var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
        Everything you need to go from keyword to ranking website.
      </p>

      <h2>Getting Started</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><a href="https://app.seoplant.io/register">Create a free account</a> — no credit card required</li>
        <li>Create your first project — enter a keyword or niche</li>
        <li>Run a competitor analysis — see who ranks and why</li>
        <li>Generate your SEO strategy — topic clusters, content calendar, keyword priorities</li>
        <li>Build and deploy your site</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>How It Works</h2>

      <h3>1. Competitor Intelligence</h3>
      <p>Enter a keyword. Our engine searches across multiple engines to find the top-ranking competitors in your niche. It crawls their websites, analyzes their SEO signals — title tags, meta descriptions, heading hierarchy, schema markup, content depth, internal linking — and generates a SWOT report showing exactly where you can beat them.</p>

      <h3>2. SEO Strategy</h3>
      <p>Real search volume data powers your strategy. See actual monthly searches, keyword difficulty scores, CPC values, and search intent for every keyword. Get a 6-month content calendar with pillar pages, cluster topics, and priority rankings — so you know exactly what to build first.</p>

      <h3>3. Content Generation</h3>
      <p>AI writes SEO-optimized articles tailored to your keywords. Each article targets specific search intent, includes proper heading hierarchy, and passes through our humanizer to read naturally. Starter plan includes 15 articles/month, Pro includes 100.</p>

      <h3>4. Programmatic SEO</h3>
      <p>Scale from 1 page to thousands. Upload a dataset (cities, products, categories) and our template engine generates unique, SEO-optimized pages for every row — with automatic internal linking and content variation to avoid duplicate content penalties.</p>

      <h3>5. Deployment</h3>
      <p>One-click deploy to your own server, or use our recommended hosting partners. Your site is standard code — you own it, you can export it, no lock-in.</p>

      <h2>Pricing & Credits</h2>
      <p>Every operation costs credits. Free accounts get 50 one-time credits — enough for 1 competitor analysis and 1 full SEO strategy plan. Paid plans include monthly credit refreshes.</p>

      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Operation</th><th>Credits</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Competitor Analysis</td><td>5</td></tr>
          <tr><td>SEO Strategy Plan</td><td>10</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Site Generation</td><td>20</td></tr>
          <tr><td>AI Article (500 words)</td><td>3</td></tr>
          <tr><td>AI Pillar Page (2000 words)</td><td>10</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Programmatic Page</td><td>1</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Deployment</td><td>5</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Rank Check (per keyword)</td><td>1</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <p style="margin-top:var(--space-lg);">See <a href="/pricing">pricing</a> for plan details and credit limits.</p>

      <h2>SEO Best Practices</h2>

      <h3>Keyword Research</h3>
      <p>Start with long-tail keywords (3-5 words). They have lower competition and higher conversion intent. Use the competitor analysis to find gaps your competitors are missing.</p>

      <h3>Content Structure</h3>
      <p>Every page should have: one H1, clear H2/H3 hierarchy, short paragraphs (2-4 sentences), bullet points for scannability, and an FAQ section. Our generator handles this automatically.</p>

      <h3>Internal Linking</h3>
      <p>Link related pages together. City pages should link to other city pages in the same country. Product pages should link to comparison pages. Our programmatic engine builds these links automatically.</p>

      <h3>Monitoring</h3>
      <p>SEO is not set-and-forget. Track your rankings, watch for content decay, and refresh underperforming pages. Pro plan includes automated rank monitoring and decay detection.</p>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>

      <h4>Can I export my site?</h4>
      <p>Yes. Generated sites are standard projects. Export the code and deploy anywhere — your own server, any cloud platform. No proprietary format.</p>

      <h4>Do I need my own server?</h4>
      <p>No. We can deploy to recommended hosting partners. If you prefer your own server, we support that too.</p>

      <h4>What's the difference from other SEO tools?</h4>
      <p>Other tools do one thing: analyze, write content, or build sites. We do all three in one pipeline — from keyword research to deployed website.</p>

      <h4>Is my data shared with AI models?</h4>
      <p>No. Your SEO data and content are private. We do not use your data to train models.</p>

    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  h2 { margin-top: var(--space-3xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-md); }
  h3 { margin-top: var(--space-xl); }
  h4 { margin-top: var(--space-lg); }
  ol { padding-left: 20px; }
  ol li { padding: 4px 0; line-height: 1.6; }
  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: var(--space-md) 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  th, td {
    padding: 10px 14px;
    text-align: left;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  th { background: var(--color-surface); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
